ANIMATE VOICE CASSETTE 04 Neon Genesis Evangelion Shinji & Asuka Version - Side B.flac
description:
![Cover Scan](https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/428273345344045057/1054213153346560111/folder.png)
This is a *raw* rip of both sides of the Neon Genesis Evangelion cassette drama released on December 1st, 1996. The main version of this online is a nicovideo upload from 2008 which suffers from poor audio quality, while this release is a lossless capture directly from the original tape. Due to the nature of the format, it suffers from audio noise throughout both sides. Side B’s general dialog/SFX sounds somewhat worse than Side A, it’s inherent to the tape but dialog is still much cleaner than the previously mentioned 2008 upload. The tape heavily relies on stereo’s two channels, with Shinji’s dialog coming from the left and Asuka’s from the right. 

**Translations from the back of the case art:**
*“The dialogue between Shinji and Asuka takes you from waking up to falling asleep. A voice of encouragement speaks softly to your dark and depressed heart, followed by a confession of love. In the midst of all this, what comes to Shinji's mind?”*

title: Space Adventure Cobra (TV 1982) - Perfect Collection LD Box Audio Tracks (v2)
description:
Audio digitally ripped by @crashoveride953
LDs acquired by @crashoveride953 & I

v2 release of the audio tracks from the Space Cobra Perfect Collection LD Box release. The previous upload—which was recorded by me—technically wasn't "recorded" the right way and it suffered from LD rot as well, resulting in some clicky audio and the decision to remove several tracks from the upload.

This release fixes that. The audio tracks were digitally recorded correctly this time by Crash_Overide and *every* disc from the box set release is included here.

Please note: unlike the v1 release, both the mono & M&E tracks are left as is, meaning they aren't separated into their own files here. The episodes are not separated as well—each of the LD's sides are recorded as their own audio track.

-Marty

description:
###  These tracks are synced to the [Dragon Box Z](https://www.kanzenshuu.com/home-video/jp/dragon-box-z1/), which are the Japanese DVDs of Dragon Ball Z released in 2003.

![alt text](https://i.ibb.co/MGWGvsS/Team-Mirolo.png)
____
![alt text](https://i.ibb.co/99p3MNH/DD3-TWf3-XYAEKUAc-format-jpg-name-900x900.jpg)

### This is most likely the final release of DBZ Broadcast audio tracks. We don't found anything else to fix.
___
### **V7 Changelog :**

- New episode 258 from Fuji TV
- Episode 093 : Short chunk of audio was missing at the beginning of PEP.
- Episode 100 (Tokai + Ishikawa): For some reason, the noise/buzz cleaning was messed up, it's like it was only applied on some part of the audio. Redone from scratch.
- Episode 137 : +70ms delay wasn't applied for that episode
- Episode 184 : -160ms shift for OP and -64ms for ED because the reference track supposed to be Dragon Box was actually Broadcast audio.
- Episode 185 : Small volume drop fixed at 22:29
- Episode 195 : Very small part of audio frequencies at 02:48 are lost, most likely during japanese broadcast airing (because both missing in Fuji and Tokai versions). Fixed with Dragon Box audio.
- Episode 194 & 264 : some frequent slight clicks removed.
- Episodes 229 & 237 : OP/ED from OST to be consistent with episode quality.
- Episode 264 : Opening was delayed by 381 ms, now fixed. NEP was +32ms compared to the rest of the episode (most likely because it was synced from another AC3 remux of Dragon Box audio, and depending on which software used, there can be 32ms difference). You can delayed your NEP subtitles by -32ms, but even if you don't, it won't really noticeable.
- Episode 273 : Opening was delayed by 600 ms, now fixed.
- Overall minor individual clicks removal and other minor fixes for several episodes (50/52/69/91/125/126/128/130/140/160/161/162/184/193/240/248/256/258/266/267/269/270/272/279/280/287/289)

___

### **What is "video sync" ?**

The audio tracks of the Japanese Dragon Box Z are not properly synced to the video. Sound effects are played later than they should (about 200 milliseconds in average). In order to fix that, we have calculated the difference (in milliseconds) between many video frames and their respective sound effects, for both parts of each episode. We've then shifted each track accordingly and called them "video synced".

So the "audio synced" tracks would be tracks matching the offical sync from Dragon Box (with it's sync issues)

Note that all delays that we calculated can be found in a [spreadsheet](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/18yqylgSPYy81HOufQZTSTHevb_bVeDuOf4isdXgNq_o/edit#gid=1791917683)

The following image (episode 101) illustrate the difference between the official sync and our fixed sync :

![alt text](https://i.ibb.co/zhBqcZX/DBOX-SYNC.png)
___
### **Notes**

- We didn't used some tracks tha Kei shared in 2021 for specific reasons. [Here is the list](https://pastebin.com/maJgvHWu) with explanations.

- Openings and Next Episode Previews have the same timings as original Dragon Box (they didn't really need to be shifted along with the rest).

- The tracks from NBS have been converted from AAC 128kbps to FLAC for syncing purposes, in case you want to give it more bitrate in lossy - or keep it in FLAC

- Opening and Endings are from Dragon Box Z R2J (better quality than Broadcast Audio, but not too much to make the episode quality sounds poor in comparison).

- [There are 40 next episode previews](https://pastebin.com/tHsKYPLm) coming from Dragon Box because in the Broadcast Audio tracks, those episodes had shorten next episode previews because of another following preview for a movie or TV Special. We filtered these Dragon Box previews with iZotope to make them a bit clearer.

- If you want to restore the original dragon box sync from these tracks, download the audio sync restoration patch [here](https://drive.google.com/uc?id=1TXGoztMJpW2clHx94VL_XILYTEunKCZ4&export=download) (tracks must be renamed 001, 002...)

___

### **Acknowledgements**

Big thanks to AnimeMaakuo, Kei and everyone that shared Japanese Broadcast Audio tracks. Thanks to HKB for syncing and cleaning all fillers tracks that we didn't do.
And thanks to everyone that helped in any possible way.

description:
Maiko Ito is a former idol, now an actress and a researcher who was active in the entertainment business since 1983 and started becoming more prominent in the 2000s as an actress. Her slightly squeaky voice, paired with catchy backing tracks make for a good idol kayo experience. At the time, her label was CBS/Sony, the same as Seiko Matsuda. 
In the 2010s, she studied for a degree in medicine and robotics, then getting a master's degree and a doctorate as well as the decade went by. In 2019, she officially became a researcher for ExaWizards, an AI-related company.
Her life is pretty intriguing, and that makes her career more impressing for me, so I'm happy that I got ahold of presumably all of her recordings/sound sources for when she was an idol. Included here are her four studio albums, plus extra non-album tracks as bonus tracks. Compared to other idols, she might be a tad on the underrated side as her chart placings at the time weren't exactly to take note about, but the quality of her music is still pretty great! Please enjoy! :>

description:
Yellow Magic Orchestra / YMO:  is a Japanese electronic music band formed in Tokyo in 1978 by Haruomi Hosono, Yukihiro Takahashi and Ryuichi Sakamoto [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yellow_Magic_Orchestra)
Sketch Show: The early 2000s saw Hosono and Takahashi reunited in a project called Sketch Show [Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sketch_Show_(band))
HASYMO / Human Audio Sponge: In August 2007, the band once again reformed, taking the name HASYMO or HAS/YMO, combining the names of Human Audio Sponge and Yellow Magic Orchestra

Album Collection released until 2022/12 
Studio albums (all) (newer remastered versions by Bob Ludwig, except for 1993 Technodon album) 
Remix albums (all)
Singles and EPs (selected) (only non released tracks in Studio/Remix albums)
Live albums (not included... generally i don't like live albums...) 

Almost all the albums are in lossless quality (if you heave any of the lossy albums in lossless let me know)
![Yellow Magic Orchestra](https://i.imgur.com/micW0eU.png)

This is a collection from various sources, like;
https://zip.flac-album.com
https://asiamediadl.com
https://rutracker.org
and many others. 

If you heave condition, buy the original albums to support the artists.

Collection organized for better viewing in MediaMonkey, MusicBee and PLEX players.

description:
![Missing link](https://some-stuffs.com/assets/blog/images/Utena-OST-04.webp)

Remake of [this torrent](https://nyaa.si/view/1509729) from a few days ago for Revolutionary Girl Utena's 25th anniversary. It was brought to my attention that I used improper rips, so I ripped my own CD. Threw in scans (not my own; taken from Empty Movement) upon suggestion, too. Named the files in romaji on a whim when ripping and then I didn't want to retake the cue and log so I left them as-is under the justification that it'll make resharing simpler. An English tracklist is included for your convenience and in case you desire to rename the files. Copy of the v1's description:

This release includes the twelve tracks from Utena OST CD 04, and lyrics on external text files for the ten tracks that feature vocals. This CD includes mixes of songs from the first two arcs performed by Universal Gravitation, who sang the Apocalypse arc duel songs, as well as two songs that did play in the show: the Apocalypse version of Zettai Unmei Mokushiroku, and Missing Link, the insert song from the finale. Two songs here haven't featured in our releases yet (tracks 3 and 4), so their lyrics may not be final (though we want to give the early duel songs another pass eventually, so strictly speaking any lyrics here are liable to change in the final series batch). Many thanks to Cala and CL3 for all their excellent work on the songs that have played in the episodes we've released so far, and many thanks to bluesun for his insightful input on all the songs I asked for help with. I am most grateful for the extremely-short-notice help with Missing Link, since it was the one song I didn't have in a presentable state.

description:
Although best known as an actress, she had a stint as a singer between 1982 and 1983, releasing one album and three singles. Her debut album, ironically subtitled, "Marumi Shiraishi First" has been re-evaluated recently as a contribution to City Pop. Due to that, Victor re-released her recordings a few months ago as part of their "Female City Pop Selections" series. This "discography" uses the remaster for said 2022 reissue but re-tagged to separate the bonus 1983 single from the album. She recently held a live event where she sang all the songs on the album, and successfully fundraised money to release said performance on DVD. All of the songs are also included on Spotify, albeit under the compilation name "Marumi Shiraishi Collection", which was released in 2004. The tracklisting for has been altered to include the singles first, then album tracks. Enjoy! :>

- ***RESEED*** and fixed some typos and inaccuracies from the latest version of this torrent (2020). Your contribution in this respect was very important. Thank you.

***Kazuya Terashima*** 寺嶋 一弥 (October 13, 1958 – October 6, 2020), known by his pen name ***Izumi Matsumoto*** まつもと泉, was a Japanese manga artist best known for ***Kimagure Orange Road***. His career started in 1982, publishing his comic ***Milk Report*** in the manga magazine ***Weekly Shōnen Jump***. But real success came in 1984, publishing ***Kimagure Orange Road*** in the same magazine. He revealed that he was afflicted with a cerebrospinal fluid disease (stemming from a car accident when he was three years old) that forced him to take six years off work, and he hoped to bring attention to this disorder through his manga. On November 3, 2019, Terashima revealed that he had been diagnosed with spinal stenosis. Matsumoto died at 61 on October 6, 2020.

description:
## This a reupload. Some tracks have been reduced in volume for uniformity (HKB tracks and a few others)

###  These tracks are synced to the [Dragon Box Z](https://www.kanzenshuu.com/home-video/jp/dragon-box-z1/), which are the Japanese DVDs of Dragon Ball Z released in 2003.

![alt text](https://i.ibb.co/MGWGvsS/Team-Mirolo.png)
____
![alt text](https://i.ibb.co/99p3MNH/DD3-TWf3-XYAEKUAc-format-jpg-name-900x900.jpg)

### This is most likely the final release of DBZ Broadcast audio tracks. We didn't found anything else to fix.
___
### **V7 Changelog :**

- New episode 258 from Fuji TV
- Negative gain applied to louder tracks for more uniformity (mostly HKB tracks)
- Episode 093 : Short chunk of audio was missing at the beginning of PEP.
- Episode 100 (Tokai + Ishikawa): For some reason, the noise/buzz cleaning was messed up, it's like it was only applied on some part of the audio. Redone from scratch.
- Episode 137 : +70ms delay wasn't applied for that episode
- Episode 184 : -160ms shift for OP and -64ms for ED because the reference track supposed to be Dragon Box was actually Broadcast audio.
- Episode 185 : Small volume drop fixed at 22:29
- Episode 195 : Very small part of audio frequencies at 02:48 are lost, most likely during japanese broadcast airing (because both missing in Fuji and Tokai versions). Fixed with Dragon Box audio.
- Episode 194 & 264 : some frequent slight clicks removed.
- Episodes 229 & 237 : OP/ED from OST to be consistent with episode quality.
- Episode 264 : Opening was delayed by 381 ms, now fixed. NEP was +32ms compared to the rest of the episode (most likely because it was synced from another AC3 remux of Dragon Box audio, and depending on which software used, there can be 32ms difference). You can delayed your NEP subtitles by -32ms, but even if you don't, it won't really noticeable.
- Episode 273 : Opening was delayed by 600 ms, now fixed.
- Overall minor individual clicks removal and other minor fixes for several episodes (50/52/69/91/125/126/128/130/140/160/161/162/184/193/240/248/256/258/266/267/269/270/272/279/280/287/289)

___

### **What is "video sync" ?**

The audio tracks of the Japanese Dragon Box Z are not properly synced to the video. Sound effects are played later than they should (about 200 milliseconds in average). In order to fix that, we have calculated the difference (in milliseconds) between many video frames and their respective sound effects, for both parts of each episode. We've then shifted each track accordingly and called them "video synced".

So the "audio synced" tracks would be tracks matching the offical sync from Dragon Box (with it's sync issues)

Note that all delays that we calculated can be found in a [spreadsheet](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/18yqylgSPYy81HOufQZTSTHevb_bVeDuOf4isdXgNq_o/edit#gid=1791917683)

The following image (episode 101) illustrate the difference between the official sync and our fixed sync :

![alt text](https://i.ibb.co/zhBqcZX/DBOX-SYNC.png)
___
### **Notes**

- We didn't used some tracks tha Kei shared in 2021 for specific reasons. [Here is the list](https://pastebin.com/maJgvHWu) with explanations.

- Openings and Next Episode Previews have the same timings as original Dragon Box (they didn't really need to be shifted along with the rest).

- The tracks from NBS have been converted from AAC 128kbps to FLAC for syncing purposes, in case you want to give it more bitrate in lossy - or keep it in FLAC

- Opening and Endings are from Dragon Box Z R2J (better quality than Broadcast Audio, but not too much to make the episode quality sounds poor in comparison).

- [There are 40 next episode previews](https://pastebin.com/tHsKYPLm) coming from Dragon Box because in the Broadcast Audio tracks, those episodes had shorten next episode previews because of another following preview for a movie or TV Special. We filtered these Dragon Box previews with iZotope to make them a bit clearer.

- If you want to restore the original dragon box sync from these tracks, download the audio sync restoration patch [here](https://drive.google.com/uc?id=1TXGoztMJpW2clHx94VL_XILYTEunKCZ4&export=download) (tracks must be renamed 001, 002...)

___

### **Acknowledgements**

Big thanks to AnimeMaakuo, Kei and everyone that shared Japanese Broadcast Audio tracks. Thanks to HKB for syncing and cleaning all fillers tracks that we didn't do.
And thanks to everyone that helped in any possible way.

Lossless Voice Packs v3.1.1
Uploaded on behalf of /t/ anon.

Changelog

2023.01.01 (`/t/thread/1196112#p1196226`)
- Replaced the files in ホロライブ×ファミマ 2022-05 & ホロライブ×ファミマ 2022-08 with files ripped from the site; thanks to `/t/thread/1180808#p1186657`
- Still need tagging info for Chloe's クリスマスデート Membership Voice and Bae's "A Winter's Dream" Membership Voice
- Holo ID packs are confirmed to be mp3 now
- 夜空メル 活動4周年記念 was posted in flac, so I added it to the unverified list

2022.11.09 (`/t/thread/1180808#p1184528`)
- Added:
    - ときのそら 活動5周年記念
    - 赤井はあと 活動4周年記念
    - 百鬼あやめ 活動4周年記念
    - 角巻わため 誕生日記念2022
    - Missing ホロライブ夏休みボイス2022 voices
    - Reimu Endou Birthday Goods & Voice 2022
    - Petra's "Christmas Voice 2021" wallpapers
    - Petra's "Good Night & Good Morning Voice 2022"
    - "November Seasonal Voice 2022 Vol.1" - Group EN
    - "November Seasonal Voice 2022 Vol.2" - Group EN
- Fixed folder names for 百鬼あやめボイス(1)and がうる・ぐら 誕生日記念2022
- Added a "Missing" folder to the Hololive directory; it contains the images and descriptions for the missing voice packs. Hopefully this promotes visibility, and it will make my job easier should they ever get posted. The URL's are still listed in the Missing Voices.txt

2022.11.02 (`/t/thread/1180808#p1182638`)
- Updated all FLAC files to FLAC 1.4.0
- Split the "Notes & Unverified" text from the last version into their own individual files
- Thanks to https://nyaa.si/view/1532430#com-1 for pointing out that Coco's bonus voice wasn't noted as missing. This has been corrected.
- ホロライブインドネシア3期生 活動半年記念 is likely a transcode, unless 128kbps mp3 is the new standard for Holo ID
- Nijisanji has decided to rename their "All-Purpose Voice" sets. I was not able to acquire all of the assets prior to this change, so some of the images will use the new name (the old ones were wiped). Ironically, all the page descriptions were unchanged. I'm not interested in retroactively renaming all the existing "All-Purpose Voice" sets, so I will probably keep using "All-Purpose Voice" going forward. You're free to change them if you wish.
- Collab audio notes:
    - I found out that the voice files for the old Azur Lane collab were just sitting on the wiki, so I added the whole set + images. The collab was officially titled 幻想と真実の二重奏 and is in the ホロライブ×アズールレーン「幻想と真実の二重奏」 folder. The old "propose" files are the "Pledge" files.
    - Following this, I attempted to look for sources for the other game collabs. I was able to find a mod for World of Warships, but I have no idea if the included .wem files are the true source files or not. .wem is technically a custom vorbis format, and one I have little experience with. Foobar can play these without issue, likely due to the [vgmstream component](https://github.com/vgmstream/vgmstream). I used a [simple converter](https://www.nexusmods.com/monsterhunterworld/mods/1912) to make them standard .ogg vorbis files for better compatibility. These files technically are not bit identical to the .wem's, but they are identical to the existing files in the previous versions of the lossless voice pack torrent, so either that is normal, or a similar/identical process was used for them.
    - I tried to find sauce for the fubuki_game_sound folder as well and came up empty. An anon from the Fubuki thread on /vt/ had some luck, and the filenames seem to match sound filenames that are used for Minecraft. I don't recall there being a Minecraft collab, and I see no mentions of one on either the EN or JP wikis, so this is potentially a custom Minecraft mod or something. It originally appeared in https://nyaa.si/view/1469817. I would ask Holopirates directly, but I am not involved with them.
    - The ホロライブ×ファミマ and ホロライブ×ローソン stuff is likely all recordings of the original files, and therefore transcodes. Due to their nature, this is probably as good as it's going to get, and some of them are no longer obtainable anyway.

2022.05.21 (`/t/thread/1140010#p1142270`)
- Fixed subfolders for Council and IRyS
- Added ムーナ・ホシノヴァ誕生日記念2021
- Verified アキ・ローゼンタール 誕生日記念2022, 天音かなた活動2周年記念, 姫森ルーナ 活動2周年記念, and 尾丸ポルカ 誕生日記念2022

Earlier this year, as it's the 40th anniversary of Akina's debut, Warner decided to do a reissue campaign of all of her albums when she was in Reprise records. As of this point, four of her studio albums, one EP, and one compilation has been reissued with all having its karaoke counterparts as the second disc and some bonus tracks (mostly b-sides) were also included. Honestly, this is the perfect example on how people should reissue their albums so kudos to them. Two versions of said remaster exist, the regular CD one (which includes bonus karaoke disc) and the 24-bit/92khz digital-only one (although with only the bonus tracks, and not the karaoke tracks). Both editions have been included, so enjoy! :>
P.S. as I'm pretty sure the rest of the albums will be reissued in the following months; follow-up torrents will be created as well to accommodate those releases.

Also included is her Singles CD compilation which instead of using the Lacquer MasterSound Remaster, uses a Flat Master instead, which is pretty cool. Like last time, both CD version and Hi-Res version have been included here, so enjoy and have a tender x'mas!

description:
![alt text](https://i.ibb.co/MGWGvsS/Team-Mirolo.png)

**First and foremost, we want to sincerely thank everyone who shared broadcast audio tracks with all of us (Kei17, AnimeMaakuo, HKB, Dougo13...).**
This torrent gather almost all raw broadcast audio tracks shared online these past years. We synced & clean the better versions of them in our releases, except from some Fuji tracks for DBZ.

Considering the amount of work it needed, we ignored fillers episodes and some other tracks (reasons in the list below)
[List of unused tracks](https://pastebin.com/maJgvHWu). There are some of them that you can still use with some work. Note that we didn't analyzed tracks marked as filler at all, so you may find the best tracks in there.

To sum up, all tracks from the list above are located in `DBZ - Raw Broadcast Audio tracks > DBZ Broadcast Audio - FUJI TV - FLAC > Shared in 2021 by Kei`, as well as the `Not analyzed tracks` folder.

We most likely retire from broadcast audio syncing and cleansing. In case there are new BA tracks that emerge in the future, we leave you these two following video tutorials if you want to work on them.

Also I think it's important to archive all those tracks, who knows when we'd need them for a fix or something else.

## Tutorials

#### **How to sync Broadcast audio tracks**

[![IMAGE ALT TEXT HERE](https://i.ibb.co/S5Dssyp/61c8723349e5a-fbutube-How-to-sync-two-audio-tracks-Dragon-Ball-Broadcast-audio-example-2-4-screensho.png)](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=uj7dOKoVIQU)


#### **How to clean broadcast audio tracks**
[![IMAGE ALT TEXT HERE](https://i.ibb.co/K0HfK80/61c87182e33ae-fbutube-How-to-clean-old-broadcast-audio-tracks-from-Dragon-Ball-0-26-screenshot-1.png)](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qCSPbzQ4nZI)



### Notes 

In tracks, you may encounter audio alerts from the broadcasting channel. Here are samples of how they sound :

description:
This torrent contains audio tracks to all the episodes included in the Perfect Collection LD box set for the 1982 Cobra TV anime, recorded by me.

Exclusive to this LD set is an extra audio track included in all episodes that contains the M&E (music & sound effects) with no dialogue—not only is it generally in higher quality compared to the show's final mix, but these audio tracks weren't even included in any of the show's JP/US DVD & BD releases at all. Bummer!
Also included in the set (which you can find in this torrent as well) is the M&E to the English pilot version for Cobra.

These come in two versions:
Multi-Track—this is how it was presented on the LD. Show's original mono mix on the left channel, and the M&E on the right channel.
M&E—self-explanatory. Copied and pasted the right channel onto the left for these ones.

FYI: do not consider this torrent to be the "ultimate" / final version of these audio tracks.

-The LDs contain digital audio. The way I went about recording these, well—it's satisfactory enough but I didn't record it "the true way", the way being using equipment that allows you to capture every single "bit" or whatever. I don't have time for that.
-I only included the M&E for the final episode here. Unfortunately I didn't realize until the last second that the last LD in this set was rotting already, and as a result the audio tracks for the final episode aren't in good quality. The mono mix is REALLY clicky, so I left that out. It doesn't click as much in the M&E track but it's still there. These sets kinda cost a lot of money, and quite frankly I can't be bothered to purchase another set just to record one episode—would be a different story if LD sets sold very easily but sadly that is not the case. Anyone else is more than likely to get their own copy and record it though (assuming that ever happens soon...)

That's all. Enjoy!
-Marty

description:
Her third studio release in 1983, seventh overall in her discography and her last album of new material recorded for Discomate (unless if you count "Junko The Live" from 1984). 
Pretty amazing year for her to be honest, considering also released that time was her more-underrated album, "Lonely Girl" which I guess is the start of Junko exploring the more "City Pop" style with a mix of her usual Adult Contemporary (AOR) music. Now that this album is a celebrated treasure, mostly due to the song "黄昏のBay City" which YouTube decided to let us discover just a few years ago. 
For this expanded edition, I decided to add some bonus tracks to this release including the B-sides to the two singles released for this album, "Naturally" and yes, "黄昏のBay City". Also included are the two single A-sides' respective single edits (shorter edit for " 黄昏のBay City" while "Naturally" has a cleaner fade-out), the superior 12" single version for "黄昏のBay City" and more edits of "綿雪 & 銀紙星" and "No!" since those two are segued together in the original album. Now that's all out of the way, let us enjoy this magnificent City Pop album :>

Tracklisting ("*" means it's a personal favourite):

1. Follow Me (*)
2. Naturally
3. 黄昏のBay City (*)
4. 陽だまりのあなた
5. 抱きしめてあげる (*)
6. 綿雪 & 銀紙星 (コットン・スノーにペイパー・スター) (*)
7. No!
8. ハートブレイクホテルで朝食を (*)
9. Full Moon (*)
10. Two Notes Samba (*)

Bonus Tracks (compiled by me):

11. 夕映え (B-side to "Naturally")
12. Lady-Ready (B-side to "黄昏のBay City") (*)
13. 黄昏のBay City (Special Midnight Version / 12" Extended Disco Version)
14. Naturally (Single Version)
15. 黄昏のBay City (Single Version)
16. 綿雪 & 銀紙星 (コットン・スノーにペイパー・スター) (Unsegued Edit)
17. No! (Unsegued Edit)

description:
Yoshiko Miyazaki is mostly known for being a model and actress, but in the early years of her career, she was also an idol of sorts. She was in the Victor label from 1981 to 1983, then decided to focus on her acting career instead. In 2021, she released a box attaining to her 40th anniversary debuting as a singer, including most (if not all) of her songs from the time period. The set also includes new songs recorded in the year.
This discography obtains all the tracks taken from the box-set and re-tagged by actual album. Please enjoy :>

title: Rahxephon Complete OST FLAC
description:
I finished the series last night (1/3) and really enjoyed the OST and amazing OP/ED as well as the show as well!!

Basically the better ending of The End of Evangelion!

One of the earliest songs from Maaya Sakamoto! Have a listen (Hemisphere).

I check the search bar. The FLAC share is a combined file (which I think is a no no) and there's only MP3 for the albums.

So now we finally have FLAC Album for single songs.

Here's the Artbook as well

https://nyaa.si/view/1473848

I watched OZC’s encodes:

https://nyaa.si/?f=0&c=0_0&q=Rahxephon+OZC

I haven't tried others like UQW and Moozzi2. The show does still look like it was upscaled from DVD (Instead of native high BD resolution).

Go watch it!! I love the designs from Yamada Akihiro (https://twitter.com/ya_kawaraban)

Quon has one of the best character design on any medium!

![alt text](https://i.imgur.com/BJmovWD.jpg "Logo Title Text 1")

I'll seed for a week or so then I'll let the seeders do their thing.

Here's also DDL so you have many chances of getting this in the coming years:

title: Schwarz Stein (シュヴァルツ シュタイン) - Discography (2002 - 2019) FLAC
description:
![](https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/visualkei/images/1/12/Schwarz_stein.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/1000?cb=20160117184620&path-prefix=es)

Schwarz Stein is a Japanese electronic project founded by Kaya (vocals) and Hora (keyboard & synth). Following a 10 year split, the band have reunited.

Formed as Rudolf Steiner in 2001 in Japan. Signed with former Malice Mizer's Mana label, Midi:Nette, and became Schwarz Stein (Black Stone in broken german) in 2002. On Feb 2 2004, two weeks before the release of Artificial Hallucination, they announced their split-up. 
Schwarz Stein reformed in 2011 to release the 'Recurrence of Hallucination' mini CD July 20th and to play a 10 year anniversary show with the same name on July 31st 2011. Another one off show was announced for 2012.
They revived again in March of 2014, rather unexpectedly, and announced the release of a new single "GEBET." Additionally, Kaya announced that he was also going to be in a new band named FEMME FATALE.

Enjoy one of my favourite idols from my favourite label, Canyon Records! :>

description:
![atl text](https://i.postimg.cc/kXVFZ6K3/Imagen-principal-castellano.png)

Finally, the complete Galician Broadcast Audio of original Dragon Ball. This release is perfectly compatible with SoM release: https://nyaa.si/view/1436046
You must to adapt Galician audio to original 23.976fps or video and japanese audio to 25fps.

**Why this?**

As Overdrive said: Selecta Vision’s audios are rubbish: degraded, poorly edited, pitch changes, etc…
In the recents BluRay, Selecta Vision's audio are from Salvat DVDs, and not from original Betacam masters. 

**How has the audio been treated?**

In this release I tried to do a proper work of the original Salvat audios. The process include a perfect Dragon Box sync, in base to Team Mirolo video-sync and a careful edition of the censored scenes. The japanese audio have an EQ to match the censored scenes to Galician audio. In this way, it has been possible to obtain a homogeneous audio

Here an example of Dragon Ball Z(coming soon):

https://streamable.com/6m9zad

Episodes 106 and 110 have an extract of TDT audio, because this scenes are not in Salvat DVDs(and, of course, in Selecta Vision's editions):

https://streamable.com/ypjio5
https://streamable.com/7zw70q

**The audio have noise reduction?**

No. I only deleted the PAL background beep, that is in the frecuency 15625:
![alt text](https://i.postimg.cc/442mrWQn/Adobe-Audition-27-04-2022-18-21-12-2.png)
![alt text](https://i.postimg.cc/RFXNCdrs/Adobe-Audition-27-04-2022-18-21-26-2.png)

**V2 changes**:

-Added new TDT audio for censored scenes of episodes 106 and 110
-Fixed sync issue in episode 121
-Fixed censorship edition in episode 142(thanks to Emilio Fernández for notice that)
-Added 23.976 sync version(only in AC3)
-Added forced subtitles for censored scenes(only for 25fps sync version)(thanks to Emilio Fernández)

**Special thanks to Kyaneos, Sondela89, Srmusico, Hobbes, Trasancos, Emilio Fernández and Anion**

**Other releases:**
* Dragon Ball Z - Spanish Broadcast Audio [210-217, 221-227] [VHS Cuatro] [Dragon Box sync] [FLAC]: https://nyaa.si/view/1517148
* Dragon Ball Z - Boing España [2011-2012] [150+- episodes]: https://nyaa.si/view/1507440
*  Dragon Ball Z - Galician Broadcast Video [TVG 2007-2019]: https://nyaa.si/view/1499567
* Dragon Ball Z Complete Galician Broadcast Audio [TVG-TVG2] [Dragon Box sync] [FLAC]: https://nyaa.si/view/1529536

description:
Lossless Voice Packs v2.11
Uploaded on behalf of /t/ anon.

Changelog

2022.11.02 (`/t/thread/1180808#p1182638`)
- Updated all FLAC files to FLAC 1.4.0
- Split the "Notes & Unverified" text from the last version into their own individual files
- Thanks to https://nyaa.si/view/1532430#com-1 for pointing out that Coco's bonus voice wasn't noted as missing. This has been corrected.
- ホロライブインドネシア3期生 活動半年記念 is likely a transcode, unless 128kbps mp3 is the new standard for Holo ID
- Nijisanji has decided to rename their "All-Purpose Voice" sets. I was not able to acquire all of the assets prior to this change, so some of the images will use the new name (the old ones were wiped). Ironically, all the page descriptions were unchanged. I'm not interested in retroactively renaming all the existing "All-Purpose Voice" sets, so I will probably keep using "All-Purpose Voice" going forward. You're free to change them if you wish.
- Collab audio notes:
    - I found out that the voice files for the old Azur Lane collab were just sitting on the wiki, so I added the whole set + images. The collab was officially titled 幻想と真実の二重奏 and is in the ホロライブ×アズールレーン「幻想と真実の二重奏」 folder. The old "propose" files are the "Pledge" files.
    - Following this, I attempted to look for sources for the other game collabs. I was able to find a mod for World of Warships, but I have no idea if the included .wem files are the true source files or not. .wem is technically a custom vorbis format, and one I have little experience with. Foobar can play these without issue, likely due to the [vgmstream component](https://github.com/vgmstream/vgmstream). I used a [simple converter](https://www.nexusmods.com/monsterhunterworld/mods/1912) to make them standard .ogg vorbis files for better compatibility. These files technically are not bit identical to the .wem's, but they are identical to the existing files in the previous versions of the lossless voice pack torrent, so either that is normal, or a similar/identical process was used for them.
    - I tried to find sauce for the fubuki_game_sound folder as well and came up empty. An anon from the Fubuki thread on /vt/ had some luck, and the filenames seem to match sound filenames that are used for Minecraft. I don't recall there being a Minecraft collab, and I see no mentions of one on either the EN or JP wikis, so this is potentially a custom Minecraft mod or something. It originally appeared in https://nyaa.si/view/1469817. I would ask Holopirates directly, but I am involved with them.
    - The ホロライブ×ファミマ and ホロライブ×ローソン stuff is likely all recordings of the original files, and therefore transcodes. Due to their nature, this is probably as good as it's going to get, and some of them are no longer obtainable anyway.

2022.05.21 (`/t/thread/1140010#p1142270`)
- Fixed subfolders for Council and IRyS
- Added ムーナ・ホシノヴァ誕生日記念2021
- Verified アキ・ローゼンタール 誕生日記念2022, 天音かなた活動2周年記念, 姫森ルーナ 活動2周年記念, and 尾丸ポルカ 誕生日記念2022
- Notes paste updated to reflect this: https://pastebin.com/DXhGr9Kv ([archive](https://web.archive.org/web/20220524002438/https://pastebin.com/DXhGr9Kv))

2022.05.18 (`/t/thread/1140010#p1141407`)
- See important changes over V1.1: https://pastebin.com/4pNwytKd ([archive](https://web.archive.org/web/20220524002359/https://pastebin.com/4pNwytKd))

2021.11.05 (`/t/thread/1085919#p1085934`)

- Fixed Subaru and Suisei track numbers for Hololive Valentine's Day Voice 2020

description:
# **_Revue☆Starlight Music Collection v3_**
## *「少女☆歌劇 レヴュースタァライト」サウンド・コレクション*

![wakarimasu](https://www.themoviedb.org/t/p/original/57pNyrLMVLKBDIscJMOk7YCldBT.jpg "wakarimasu")

### Updated because the last collection doesn't include any Gekijouban music, and I figured everyone else should benefit from my work. Should have most retail releases, and some blu-ray bonuses. Rename v2 folder to v3, delete deprecated folders and recheck, should update easily. 

### Based off of https://nyaa.si/view/1372374 with the following changes:
```
All new and improved albums have been tagged with Musicbrains Picard. I would have put every album through it, but I know most people would prefer to have their torrent client work with the new revision as is. Some tracks from the albums with multiple versions are stored in only one of the folders. From my understanding, these tracks are bit identical between the versions. 

[2018.10.17] 「少女☆歌劇 レヴュースタァライト」オリジナルサウンドトラック [FLAC] is now complete (entire OST in 48kHz/24bits).
[2019.08.09] 「少女☆歌劇 レヴュースタァライト」インストアルバム「ラ レヴュー・オン・ボワット」 [320k mp3] has been replaced with [2019.08.09] 「少女☆歌劇 レヴュースタァライト」インストアルバム「ラ レヴュー・オン・ボワット」 [FLAC]

Added the following albums:
[2021.06.30] 私たちはもう舞台の上 [FLAC]
[2021.07.14] サイカイ合図【星ver.】 [FLAC]
[2021.07.14] サイカイ合図【花ver.】 [FLAC]
[2021.07.21] 劇場版 少女☆歌劇 レヴュースタァライト 劇中歌アルバムVol.1 [FLAC]
[2021.07.21] 劇場版 少女☆歌劇 レヴュースタァライト 劇中歌アルバムVol.2 [FLAC]
[2021.12.22] 舞台裏のレヴュー [FLAC]
[2022.04.20] Delight to me! (Delight ver.) [FLAC]
[2022.04.20] Delight to me! (エーデル ver.) [FLAC]
[2022.09.21] 「少女☆歌劇 レヴュースタァライト」レヴューアルバム「アルカナ・アルカディア」 [FLAC]
[2022.10.12] Regalia -継承-_アフレぐ!~Aufregendes leben~ [FLAC]
```

title: [2017.08.16] 打上花火(Uchiage Hanabi) - DAOKO (FLAC 24bit／48+96kHz)
description:
Single: 48kHz
Album: 96kHz (Uchiage Hanabi/打上花火 Only) 

「打上花火」（うちあげはなび）は、日本のシンガー・DAOKOの楽曲。米津玄師が手掛けたこの曲は、2017年8月16日にトイズファクトリーより、「DAOKO×米津玄師」名義で発売された。楽曲は新房昭之監督のアニメ映画『打ち上げ花火、下から見るか? 横から見るか?』の主題歌に起用された。

"Uchiage Hanabi" (Japanese: 打上花火, official English is "Fireworks") is a song by Daoko and Kenshi Yonezu released in August 2017. "Uchiage Hanabi" means "launching fireworks". The song is used for the anime film Fireworks and the album Thank You Blue. There are two solo versions, Yonezu's solo version released for Bootleg for minimalist rearrangement, and Daoko's solo version for Shiteki Ryoko. It ranked number one in Billboard Japan Hot Animation for 25 weeks.[1] It won Song of the Year of Space Shower Music Awards in 2018.

Album Collection released until 2022/12 
Studio albums (all) (newer remastered versions by Bob Ludwig, except for 1993 Technodon album) 
Remix albums (all)
Singles and EPs (selected) (only non released tracks in Studio albums)
Live albums (not included... generally i don't like live albums...) 

Almost all the albums are in lossless quality (if you heave any of the lossy albums in lossless let me know)

https://asiamediadl.com

and many others. 

If you heave condition, buy the original albums to support the artists.

Collection organized for better viewing in MediaMonkey, MusicBee and PLEX players.

Ver. [2020.12.31]
- [2020.11.11] 田所あずさ｜ヤサシイセカイ

Sometimes, a seiyuu releases such a number of CDs during her career that it may be difficult not to get lost. Therefore, for this collection (and possibly also for the next ones) I wanted to try something different: I decided to divide the CDs labelling them into “Eras”. Musically speaking, an “Era” is composed of all single CDs that precede the release of an album or mini-album (which, usually, includes some or all of the songs included in these singles). When the album is released, an Era ends and a new one begins starting from the next single. Every Era is named after the title of the album that concludes it and, normally, gathers songs that are not present in previous Eras, nor will be in future ones. In this case, Azusa’s discography is indeed divided into four Eras, one for each of her albums.

The first modern full-scale idol group to exist before Onyanko Club. They were the in-house group of variety show, All Night Fuji, which ran from 1983 to 1991. The group had sub-groups as well, the most popular being the Okawari Sisters. Most of the original cast graduated at around March 1985 and future generations failed to capture the moderate success they had hence why the frequency of releases lessened drastically since 1985. Not everything is included here sadly, but I can say around 85 percent of their work is here, enjoy! :>

スタジオジブリが誇る歴史的大作アニメーションのサウンドトラックピアノ版

日本のアニメ制作会社の代表ともいえるスタジオジブリが、1997年に公開した長編アニメーション映画『もののけ姫』。もちろん監督は宮崎駿で、構想に16年、制作に3年をかけた大作として話題を集めた。結果、興行収入193億円を記録し当時の日本映画の興行記録を塗り替える歴史的作品となった。今作『Good Sleep Music Studio Ghibli Princess Mononoke Soundtracks Relaxing Piano Covers』は、その『もののけ姫』のサウンドトラックのピアノバージョンだ。日本の中世(室町時代頃)を舞台にしている物語らしく、世が戦国時代へ向かう動乱期を思わせるマイナー調の楽曲が、映画の世界観にぴったり。ピアノカバーにより、その世界観に深みが出たことにも注目してもらいたい。

description:
A year (and some) ago, one of my first music-related torrents (that was actually of some sort of quality) was a discography one of my still most favourite singers in general, Hiromi Iwasaki. This torrent is a new (and slightly improved) version with more songs (especially after 1988 and some non-album oddities). At this point, what's not included here are her NHK recordings (usually in mono), her 1996 "Full Circle" live concert, and her "Original Karaoke" tracks (some were included in the first version, but all were removed for this one, I'll place them back in the next version!). As usual, I basically made my own "reissue" and "expanded" tracklistings, some albums remaining the same as its official counterpart, some with the same amount but different tracks, and some tracks altogether moved to other albums or removed as it did not fit the time period (very rare occurrence), or some having no bonus tracks at all. Despite that, all her important songs are here and there's a lot of content to be discovered heard from one of the leading artists of the country. Enjoy! :>

description:
She originally debuted in 1986 as an idol for For LIfe Records where she stayed and had a moderately-successful career as one until the end of 1987. She didn't release new singles for almost a year until she transferred to Pony Canyon (but not as an idol anymore) and resumed releasing recordings by the latter half of 1988. She would then release more stuff until 1995 (although she only had one release in 1995 which was taken from her 1993 album, and she also did not release anything in 1992). She then retired from the entertainment industry to focus on her growing family until her return in the industry in 2013 (she would however show herself in the public eye more the year prior). She started to release more and celebrated her 35th anniversary with a new album in 2021. 

included here are her recordings from her Pony Canyon-era plus singles, b-sides included as bonus tracks in her four albums. Enjoy and happy holidays! :>

description:
Junko Sakurada is an idol singer who debuted in 1973, alongside other hit-makers, Momoe Yamaguchi and Masako Mori (idol turned enka singer). She was active until 1983 in which she became mostly an actress until her marriage in a "Unification Church" in 1992, although her husband was picked by the church itself but since they're still together, I guess it worked well. She led a mostly private life from that point onward, releasing a book in 2006 while her music was reissued in 2008 (although copies of her albums are hard to find, hence why this isn't an album discography). For her 40th anniversary in 2013, she reappeared in the public, releasing a commemorative compilation ("Thanks 40"), then again in 2018 ("Thanks 45") although as a live compilation. She also released an album in 2018 ("My Idology"), and since her reemergence, she has been in a lot of concerts and public performances which is great! 
Included here are all of her singles (both A and B sides), released from 1973 to 1983. While it's not a complete album discography, I think 76 songs are enough to have an introduction to a great idol (while I try to look for her missing albums...), so enjoy!

![Junko Sakurada](https://i.pinimg.com/736x/93/f5/21/93f521802f61af8ae65c3b9ae221f229.jpg)

description:
Today I present to you what should be a perfectly aligned exact sample precise cut of the "new" 5.1 mix and "remastered" 2.0 legacy audio. I decided to only share the specific DEATH(true)^2 and The End of Evangelion rather than the complete DISC 07 and DISC 08 tracks that I put together since it seems likely that most people probably have either Beatrice-Raws for Revival of Evangelion or maybe some other encode but as long as it was cut on the correct chapters, it fits. Currently I watch NGE as a remux from my own JPBD discs which is why I originally made them as a complete track to fit sourcing the Khara intro and Intermission segment from DISC 08. If anyone else consumes EVA as a BD-Remux then it really is as simple as stringing it together with Audacity using the Khara intro and Intermission since I already did the pixel peeping work to get it down to the closest audio samples. I used MKVToolNix to first create an MKA for each audio track including the chapters then afterwards used the Chapter Editor to segment each of the necessary blocks of audio then foobar2000 will read Matroska files just like a cue file. For convenience if anyone wants to make a complete audio track, I have supplied the 5.1 and 2.0 Khara Intro and Intermission files in the Mega folder. I actually ended up redoing these a few times. At first I only counted frame differences and it actually worked pretty well. Then afterwards I decided to zoom in more and check because sure enough, there was still a slight variation then I adopted actually counting samples along with frames. Rather than switching to only sample counting, for me it was way easier to count frames that I already determined first then remaining slight amount in samples. When there was a hard reference point to find in the 5.1 track, I used the 2.0 track to find a good spot and vice versa. Pretty neat how the opposite tracks were able to help each other out in a sense.

Just in case anyone else wants to do this with the English tracks or if other languages are cut the same as well, I'll share my results I came up with since I documented all of it.
- DEATH(true)^2 = cut 23 frames and 43 samples from beginning + cut end to match JPBD audio (audio supplied here can substitute since I already aligned them)
- End of Evangelion = cut 28 frames and 36 samples from beginning + 134,534,756 sample starting point (or any of that blank space, that just happens to be my reference point) then cut 25 frames and 80 samples (this is after THANATOS -IF I CAN'T BE YOURS-) + add ending frames missing using JPBD audio (or cut the 5+ minutes to match the end if you didn't already leave out translated credits)
At least the version of Audacity I used had it on by default but make sure to turn off dithering since source files are already 16-bit. Before anyone says USBD has 24-bit audio, in case you didn't know from looking at the file size and bitrate, here's what eac3to has to say about it: "The original audio track has a constant bit depth of 16 bits. Superfluous zero bytes detected, will be stripped in 2nd pass. Starting 2nd pass... Decoding FLAC... Reducing depth from 24 to 16 bits..." As for the Video Format Version of 25' and 26' that has 24-bit LPCM on USBD, I have not ripped and tested it yet but I'm assuming it's still 16 within a 24 container.

I'm not sure if there has been any discussion elsewhere, but back when it was released on Netflix I realized that the Japanese audio was different from the original 5.1 renewal mix. Recently when listening to it I thought since the audio levels are really juiced up, I thought it gave the impression of audio booming in a movie theater. After that I immediately made the connection that perhaps this "international" audio is the 5.1 mix that was created when the entirety of Neon Genesis Evangelion had a theatrical run back in early 2019 I believe it was. I read through most of the booklet back when I got my Ultimate Edition and I don't remember seeing anything about this in there. As for the remastered legacy audio, it is indeed different but not as apparent as the renewal audio. If I had to guess, I'd say its probably EQ adjustments. Some spots had either less or more variation on certain parts of the waveform, like previously mentioned, making it harder to cut the dead space between 25' and 26'. I originally guess cut 50 extra samples but then in the 5.1 track I found a perfect reference point and only had to end up cutting 30 more samples. As for the TV series episodes, yes, those are indeed different as well. Awhile ago I determined 30 frames at the beginning need to be cut to match JPBD but I have not fully examined with sample counting. Some people were saying the USBD was encoded better than the JPBD. Whether that's true or not, I'm sticking with JPBD since DEATH(true)^2 is zoomed in even more on the USBD so you have even less of an already cropped image plus having the original audio tracks and credits intact for the series makes it worthwhile. Plus DEATH and REBIRTH along with its extras weren't included on international releases. Currently I am not going to be doing anything too major about the rest of the series. At first I was going to replace the ED with the originals but I actually don't mind the replaced audio on those tracks. Plus it differentiates them more from the original Japan audio tracks. Interesting enough the ADV tracks actually look like original PCM master source unlike the Manga Entertainment tracks however levels are kinda whack and I noticed some audio samples are damaged (audible cracks) so it would probably take way too much time and effort to fully restore those. And it's not my rip that broke it. I popped it in my player and sure enough it's like that on disc. The old dub is kinda nostalgic but I'm not too hung up on it. After many years of hearing and learning some Japanese, I am satisfied with listening to the Japanese audio.

Anyways, hopefully this is helpful in case anyone else is interested in the audio.
I may not be able to seed right away nor constantly so the Mega folder should help for now.

description: \n                    Judy and Mary are a pop-punk band that scored continual success in the Japanese mainstream music scene throughout the second half of the 1990s. Formed in 1992 by singer Yuki, a squeaky voiced, petulant young girl, and bass player and main writer Yoshihito Onda, the two went through several other band personnel until settling on Takuya (guitars) and Kota Igarashi (drums). With their outlandish costumes, which owed more to the giant hair-bands of Visual Kei, and Yuki's often bizarre onstage antics, the band grew from cult group to mainstream favorites: they were, like it or not, a cute version of punk, injected with the plastic stance of pop art. The kids loved it. Their debut album, J.A.M., was quite punk, but as the years went on, the pop sensibilities and growing songwriting confidence kicked in, and the band was trying on all sorts of styles: ballads, rock, pop, ska, all of it upbeat and featuring Yuki's strange lyrics. By the end of the '90s, the band had run its course, and Yuki was beginning to appear in other projects, including the group Nina, Mean Machine, and a duet with the singer Chara. In 2001, the band released their sixth and final album, Warp, and played one last show in Tokyo Dome. Several best-of compilations have been released. ~ Ted Mills\n

description:
This is the best best i could come up to trying to acquire a complete collection of the Atelier Series music released until 2022/12. (GUST Sound Team)

All the official soundtracks are present but some side and extra albums are missing, sadly... 
if you heave any missing album please share and let me know, for us to make a real complete collection \o/ 

Almost all the albums are in lossless quality (if you heave any of the lossy albums in lossless let me know) 

![T-Square](https://i.imgur.com/4YoIsoa.jpg)
Collection organized for better viewing in MediaMonkey, MusicBee and PLEX players.

This is a collection from various sources, like;
https://www.sittingonclouds.net
https://nyaa.si/view/646768
and many others. 

If you heave condition, buy the original albums to support the artists.

Tell my if you like the content and if i did everything right.
\o/ Send me a Cute Anime Girl gif \o/
Please Seed until it can be sheared in [Andromeda](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andromeda_Galaxy).

description:
![Project A-ko 2](https://i.imgur.com/ZdIAilj.jpg)


This is a lossless rip of the full original soundtrack for Project A-ko 2: Plot of the Daitokuji Financial Group (1987)... however, it is *not* from the CD!

There was an official CD released, but for whatever reason it only included 12 tracks. Later, when they released the OVA on Laserdisc, they decided to include the soundtrack on an extra digital audio track encoded with the disc, listed as the "Music Selection" track. If your player supported it, it could be used to play the film's bare soundtrack instead of the standard analog audio that mixed the music, dialog, and sound effects together to match the video.

What was interesting about this audio track is that, on top of containing all 12 tracks from the CD, it also included an additional 6 bonus tracks! The reason why this was done is unknown, but what this means is that this bonus audio track is superior to the CD in terms of music. Unfortunately, having to play music from a Laserdisc is not very convenient, especially since this disc has only became rarer over time, so most people were not aware of this peculiar audio track.

However, that all changed when Discotek put out their Blu-Ray of Project A-ko 2. As a bonus they included this "Music Selection" track as an extra audio track in the PCM format to play when watching the OVA, releasing this rare soundtrack to the world in a much more accessible way... that is, except for the fact that having to listen to music by inserting a Blu-Ray is still pretty inconvenient.

So, for your listening pleasure, this audio track was ripped from the disc and put into Audacity, where it was then split up into separate lossless FLAC files. What's more, the OVA, and by extension the total length of all the tracks is around 50 minutes long, meaning that this soundtrack can be easily burned to a CD-R. Now you can easily create you own superior version of the soundtrack!

So I combined the 2017 re-release of the album plus the alternative edits from her "Golden Best" compilation".
For further background, Marlene is a Filipina who now lives in Japan and gathered success there in the eighties. Her style is mostly AOR and Smooth Jazz with hints of City Pop every now and then.
This is her second album to hit the Oricon charts at the time (the other being the also popular album, Deja Vu), peaking at #5.

description:
Thanksgiving is the day where we reflect on what we are most grateful for. Be it family, friends, loved ones, the roof over your head or at least the tasty feast that awaits. If none apply, perhaps some music can make it a little less shitty. (Saccharine speech over)

Got another CD rip for you guys. Not as diverse of a selection this time, even some overlap with my previous uploads but there's enough new there to not make it overly redundant. This time it's not only OPs/EDs there's some insert songs sprinkled in. There's even a bonus DVD included that has a compilation of the OPs/EDs of the series' represented on the CD. For some of the series', it may be the highest quality footage of them yet uploaded to the web. 

Since I didn't want to clutter things too much with the track titles I decided to put it here. The tracks are grouped by which series they hail from--

1 is Sennin Buraku, 2-5 from Tetsujin 28, 6-10 from Eightman, 11+12 from Super Jetter, 13+14 from Space Boy Soran, 15+16 from Yuusei Shonan Papii, 17 is Yuusei Kamen, 18-20 from Gaboten Island Adventure, 21+22 from Skyers 5, 23+24 from Sasuke, and 25-28 from Ninpuu Kamui Gaiden. 

Stay tuned, there will be more to come and please seed!

現役大学生の19歳のマルチアーティスト、Vaundy。アルバムタイトル「strobo」にはストロボライトの眩しい光から「全ての始まり」という想いがこめられており、ジャケットは閃光のイメージからビビットな蛍光ピンク一色のインパクトがあるデザインとなっている。今作には「東京フラッシュ」「不可幸力」といった配信シングル曲のほか、4月18日から放送のドラマ「捨ててよ、安達さん。」のオープニング曲「Bye by me」にアルバム新録曲を加え、全11曲が収録される。変幻自在でジャンルレスなVaundyの音楽は、新時代「令和」のミュージックシーンの台風の目となること間違いないだろう。

description:

[MACO](https://ototoy.jp/_/default/a/173483)

Release date: 2022-04-06

Label: Sony Music Labels Inc.

Catalog number: SRCL12116B00Z

Album Info :

既発曲として“運命”“恋蛍”“桜の木の下”の3曲に加え、7曲をアルバム用に書き下ろし、合計10曲になる。まず1曲目になる“Promised.”は今、MACOが伝えたいメッセージを詰め込んだ。メロディラインも非常に壮大で耳に残る楽曲に仕上がっている。2曲目に続くのが“運命共同体”。1曲目からの曲調の変化に驚く人もいるのではないかと思うほどポップな楽曲になり癖になるメロディラインと歌詞が注目だ。3曲目は“愛”。MACOにとっての“愛”を表現した曲はギターの音色が印象的でどこか背中を押してくれる楽曲だ。続く、4曲目は“春一番”。タイトルの通り、春を感じさせる爽やかな楽曲。5曲目は“lonely”。口ずさみたくなるメロディと情景が浮かんでくる歌詞が特徴的な楽曲でオシャレかつ可愛いらしい楽曲だ。6曲目はAbemaTVドラマ「僕だけが17歳の世界で」の挿入歌となった“桜の木の下”。そして続く7曲目には、島田昌典氏プロデュースによる楽曲“End Love?”とつながる。その壮大なサウンドは必聴だ。8曲9曲は既発曲“恋蛍””運命”が続く。そして10曲目は“これは君への最初のラブレター”。聴けば誰もが幸せになるこの楽曲は、アルバムの最後を飾るにふさわしい内容になっている。
